# 2p_ctf_walk_own_flag — client side. Plays the BLUE team. Walks LEFT
# repeatedly across the BLUE flag at (4160, 974), then walks RIGHT
# back. If the client gets "stuck" on their own flag, the per-tick
# pelvis trail in shot_dump_tick will show the local mech's pelv_x
# stalling near x=4160 even though BTN_LEFT is being pressed.
#
# Compare to the host's log of mech=1 — if the host sees mech=1 cross
# the flag while the client log shows mech=local stuck, the bug is in
# client-side prediction.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/client_walk_own_flag
network connect 127.0.0.1:24017
name ClientBlue

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

# Settle in the lobby.
at 60  shot t60_lobby
at 140 shot t140_round_start
at 180 shot t180_settled

# Walk RIGHT through the flag. Slot 1 BLUE spawn on Crossfire (CTF) is
# spawn[5] at x=(140-12)*32=4096, west of the BLUE flag at x=4160.
# 64 px traversal at ~4.6 px/tick = ~14 ticks to reach the flag. Hold
# RIGHT through and past the flag to see if we get stuck on it.
at 200 press right
at 220 shot t220_walking_right
at 250 shot t250_at_flag_x
at 280 shot t280_past_flag_x
at 320 release right
at 330 shot t330_settled_east_of_flag

# Walk LEFT back through the flag.
at 360 press left
at 380 shot t380_walking_left
at 410 shot t410_at_flag_x_again
at 440 shot t440_past_flag_x
at 480 release left
at 490 shot t490_settled_west_of_flag

at 700 end
